0/24 is routed over the tunnel. | **Normal** – the tunnel is functional; no leakage to other hosts is observed. |\n\n### Summary of Findings\n- **All ping tests succeed with 0 % packet loss and sub‑5 ms RTTs.**  \n- **Web servers are reachable from both internal hosts,** indicating that the external router’s forwarding and RIP routes are correctly installed.  \n- **VPN server is reachable from both hosts,** and `host_1` has a fully‑configured WireGuard interface that can reach the 172.16.1.0/24 subnet.  \n- **Routing tables on every router contain the expected RIP‑derived entries** for all internal and external subnets; no duplicate or missing routes were detected.  \n- **No firewall or NAT rules are blocking traffic** on the external router or any other node.  \n- **All interfaces are up and operational** with the expected MTU and queue disciplines.\n\n### Conclusion\nThe current state of the mini‑Internet is **healthy and fully functional**. No connectivity, routing, or firewall anomalies were detected during the tests performed. All components (hosts, routers, VPN, and web servers) are operating as designed. No further action is required at this time.", "generation_info": {"model": "gpt-oss:20b", "created_at": "2025-12-16T15:24:35.449491675Z", "done": true, "done_reason": "stop", "total_duration": 16497904126, "load_duration": 60833467, "prompt_eval_count": 7564, "prompt_eval_duration": 468728993, "eval_count": 1257, "eval_duration": 12178933821, "model_name": "gpt-oss:20b"}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7564, "output_tokens": 1257, "total_tokens": 8821}}
